content.text:
[
  {
    "span": "the Warden fell three nights ago",
    "issue": "C-narrative-warden-status-consistency: The guard first states the Warden is merely away ('returns from the northern watch') and the elder later insists 'The Warden lives and is in good health.' Claiming the Warden died three nights ago contradicts both statements on the Warden's status."
  },
  {
    "span": "The elders simply haven't said so aloud yet.",
    "issue": "C-narrative-no-premature-spoiler: The guard reveals a concealed plot point (the Warden's death, not yet publicly announced) ahead of the intended reveal, potentially spoiling the elders' later address."
  },
  {
    "span": "The Warden lives and is in good health; she will address the outpost herself at dusk.",
    "issue": "C-narrative-warden-status-consistency: Directly contradicts the guard's earlier claim that the Warden 'fell three nights ago.' The Warden cannot both be dead and alive/addressing the outpost."
  }
]

